			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Marta Klein on the actions against Jews in Vilnius and Białystok and deportations to Treblinka, her escape en route to
					the camp, her rescue by a Pole, Czuliński, and the arrest of her son and his protector after their betrayal.</p>
			</abstract>
